PRIVACY POLICY
Global Recycling of Tampa Bay
Effective Date: June 9, 2026
1. Introduction
Global Recycling of Tampa Bay ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use our services or platform.
2. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information:

Personal Information: Name, email address, phone number, billing address
Payment Information: Credit card or ACH details processed securely through QuickBooks Payments
Usage Data: Pages visited, actions taken on our platform, device and browser information
Business Information: Company name, tax ID, and service history for commercial accounts

3. How We Use Your Information
We use collected information to:

Process payments and generate invoices via QuickBooks
Communicate service updates, confirmations, and receipts
Improve our platform and services
Comply with legal and regulatory obligations

4. Third-Party Services
We integrate with Intuit QuickBooks to process payments and manage accounting data. Your payment information is transmitted directly to QuickBooks and is subject to Intuit's Privacy Policy at https://www.intuit.com/privacy/statement. We do not store full payment card numbers on our servers.
5. Data Sharing
We do not sell or rent your personal information. We may share data with:

Service providers necessary to operate our platform
Legal authorities if required by law
Business successors in the event of a merger or acquisition

6. Data Security
We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your information. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
7. Your Rights
You have the right to:

Access, correct, or delete your personal information
Opt out of marketing communications
Request a copy of data we hold about you

To exercise these rights, contact us at the information below.
8. Cookies
Our platform may use cookies to enhance user experience. You may disable cookies through your browser settings, though some features may not function properly.
9. Children's Privacy
Our services are not directed to individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
10. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify users of significant changes via email or platform notice.
11. Contact
For privacy-related inquiries, contact us at:
Global Recycling of Tampa Bay
Tampa Bay, Florida
max@starqualityinc.com

